            en: "1) Open a <strong>Google Doc</strong> (or Notion page) titled \"<code>[App Name] - Vision</code>\". 2) Write a <strong>5-sentence elevator pitch</strong> in the first paragraph: product name, target user, pain it solves, difference from alternatives, success metric (e.g. \"100 active users in 3 months\"). 3) Ask an AI (Claude, ChatGPT or Gemini) <em>\"Critique this idea via the 'mom test' lens; list my assumptions\"</em> and paste the answer under a \"Risks\" heading at the bottom. 4) <strong>Make the target user concrete</strong>: write 2 personas (age, occupation, phone habits, current workaround). 5) Share the doc with <strong>Commenter</strong> access and pin the link in your README or project board."
