            en: "1) Add <strong>heading levels</strong> to the vision doc (H1: Vision, H2: Problem / Audience / Differentiator / Success Metrics / Non-goals). 2) Date-stamp each section and review monthly with a \"Is this still true?\" pass. 3) Create a <strong>permanent short link</strong> (e.g. <code>bit.ly/proj-vision</code>) for the file so it's easy to paste into AI chats. 4) Open every new AI session with this template: <em>\"Answer strictly from the Master Doc below. Flag anything missing as 'Open Question'.\"</em> then paste the full doc text. 5) After every sprint do a 10-minute <strong>vision refresh</strong>; new learnings go under a \"Changelog\" section. <span class='hint'>Keep the Master Doc under 1-2 pages; the shorter it is, the more consistent the AI stays.</span>"
