            en: "1) You tested on <strong>both a physical phone and a simulator</strong> (don't stay on simulator only; cameras, touch and network behave differently on real hardware). 2) If you're building a native app, you ran a basic performance / memory profile once with <strong>Android Studio Profiler</strong> (Android) and <strong>Xcode Instruments</strong> (iOS). 3) You wrote the build / run commands in the README (e.g. <code>flutter run</code>, <code>npm run ios</code>, <code>./gradlew assembleDebug</code>) so a new teammate can get the project running in 30 minutes."
