            release: { tr: "<strong>Firebase App Check</strong> aktif. Web için <strong>reCAPTCHA Enterprise</strong> (veya reCAPTCHA v3) provider'ı kullanılıyor; istek üreten her sayfada arka planda token alınıyor ve Firebase isteklerine ekleniyor. Sahte istemcilerin Firestore/Storage/Cloud Functions'a erişmesi engelleniyor. <strong>Standalone PWA modunda</strong> (Ana ekrana eklenmiş, tarayıcı chrome'u olmayan oturum) reCAPTCHA Enterprise score düşebilir veya invisible challenge çalışmayabilir; bu vakaya özel <code>app-check-debug-token</code> (development) veya alternatif provider (custom token + backend signature) fallback'i hazır. iOS standalone mod için ayrıca test edilmesi gerek. <span class='hint'>Native uygulamadaki Play Integrity / App Attest'in web karşılığı reCAPTCHA Enterprise. Authentication \"bu kullanıcı kim?\" sorusunu, App Check \"bu istek hangi uygulamadan?\" sorusunu cevaplar.</span>", en: "<strong>Firebase App Check</strong> is enabled. The web provider uses <strong>reCAPTCHA Enterprise</strong> (or reCAPTCHA v3); a token is fetched silently on each page making requests and attached to Firebase calls. Fake clients are blocked from Firestore/Storage/Cloud Functions. In <strong>standalone PWA mode</strong> (Add to Home Screen, no browser chrome), reCAPTCHA Enterprise scores may drop or invisible challenges may fail; a fallback is in place — <code>app-check-debug-token</code> for development or a custom-provider path (custom token + backend signature). iOS standalone mode needs separate testing. <span class='hint'>The web counterpart of Play Integrity / App Attest is reCAPTCHA Enterprise. Authentication answers \"who is the user?\"; App Check answers \"which app does this request come from?\"</span>" }
