            en: "1) Install a <strong>local notification</strong> library: Flutter <code>flutter_local_notifications</code>; React Native <code>expo-notifications</code> (works in bare RN too) or <code>react-native-notifications</code>; Swift <code>UNUserNotificationCenter</code> (built-in); Kotlin <code>NotificationManagerCompat</code> + <code>NotificationChannel</code>; Expo <code>expo-notifications</code>; PWA <code>Notification</code> API + Service Worker. 2) Ask permission <strong>at the right moment</strong>: not on first launch, but when the user tries a feature (e.g. tapping \"add reminder\"). 3) Test: schedule a \"remind me tomorrow at 9 AM\" notification and confirm it fires."
