            en: "1) Set up push infrastructure following 6.5 (device token, backend delivery). 2) When a notification is tapped, the app should open the right screen: Flutter <code>onMessageOpenedApp</code> + Navigator; RN <code>Linking</code> + deep-link config; Swift <code>UNNotificationResponse.notification.request.content.userInfo</code>; Kotlin <code>Intent</code> + PendingIntent; Expo <code>expo-router</code> deep-link; PWA <code>notificationclick</code> event + <code>clients.openWindow</code>. 3) Include which screen to open in the notification payload (e.g. <code>{ \"screen\": \"chat\", \"chat_id\": 123 }</code>). 4) For foreground notifications, render a custom in-app UI (a banner that doesn't auto-dismiss): Flutter <code>onMessage</code>; RN notification listener. 5) Test in all three states: app killed, background, foreground."
